description:
&lt;p&gt;The Coronary Care Unit is modern with 11 beds and cares for acutely unwell male and female patients with cardiac conditions. The unit is located next to a modern Cardiac Catheter Lab and cares for patients pre and post procedure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Posts are working 37.5 hours per week across 7 days &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Newly qualified nurses will be welcomed to the trust with the first years’ NMC fees paid.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for your dedication we offer a full training and preceptorship package for all new starters. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you are passionate about providing the highest standards of care and able to demonstrate our Trust values, putting our patients at the heart of everything you do, then we would like to hear from you.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note this vacancy may close before the advertised closing date if a sufficient number of suitable applications are received.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Candidates: Please be aware that you will be asked to present your original qualifications at interview stage.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;For overseas candidates wishing to apply for the job role and require immigration sponsorship, you can self-assess the likelihood of obtaining a CoS for the post on the &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;GOV.UK website.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kim Whitseide - Matron&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: kim.whiteside@wwl.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 01942 773553&lt;/p&gt;
